comments: amazing live performance in the video

Perfection
Don't need to say anything...
Anyone who's annoyed by this song lacks a soul. It's that simple. "Devil Got My Woman" is one of the best songs ever recorded.
This reminds me of Robert Johnson!
I know people that are totally annoyed by this song. For me it's an extraordinary piece of music! So lofi, yet so perfect!
maybe one of the best music tracks, EVER

Ghost World

i love skip james dont really like this version of the song tho... thankfully he had several versions of it love skip
Wow, what a guitarist!

A masterful musician.  There's a book on Skip James by Steven Calt called "I'd Rather Be The Devil".  Skip played in open Dm (aka "Spanish") tuning.  Skip also played piano.  Never heard a voice anything like it.  Magnificent.  My favorites are Cypress Grove and Crow Jane.
first time for me .great voice
that voice, those slides, somebody sure had the blues
This god damned tune made me buy a new guitar. I love it
Now I know were Al Wilson got his inspiration.
